f=Governance/board/marketplace/pre-mortem/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "pre-mortem" skill, selected fulfill catalog's pre-mortem slot board prospective failure analysis before major commitments. Chosen over phuryn/pm-skills' pre-mortem (22k★, Tigers/Paper Tigers/Elephants) because version built around PRODUCT LAUNCHES (14-day launch framing, launch-blocking classification), while one implements Gary Klein's original prospective-hindsight method explicitly scoped DECISIONS hiring, investment, partnership, resource commitments which what governance gate reviews. Matches catalog protocol directly: assume failure future date generate causes triage (likelihood impact detectability) mitigate top risks before approval tripwires. KNOWN SOURCE DEFECT, kept verbatim copy-without-cutting rule: "What Claude What You Decide" table "Skill Boundaries" section contain copy-paste text unrelated AUDIO-PRODUCTION skill source repo ("structuring audio production workflows," "script outlines," etc.). Ignore two sections executing section correct internally consistent. Flagged rather silently edited. BOUNDARY NOTE system: marcus's decision-critic red-teams proposal IMPROVE before proposed; board's pre-mortem part GATE rules it. decision passed decision-critic still goes through board's gate. --> · h1:Pre-Mortem=Imagine your project failed spectacularly—then work backward identify why. Apply Gary Klein's "prospective hindsight" technique catch failures before they happen. · wu:This Skill=**Before launching** product, campaign, major initiative, **Before making** important decision (hiring, investment, partnership), **Starting project** identify risks team hasn't considered, **When overconfident** everyone agrees plan great, **Before committing resources** significant undertaking, **In team planning** surface concerns people hesitate share · h2:Methodology Foundation=\| Aspect \| Details \| · h2:Methodology Foundation=\|--------\|---------\| · h2:Methodology Foundation=\| **Source** \| Gary Klein (1989), cognitive psychologist, naturalistic decision making pioneer \| · h2:Methodology Foundation=\| **Expert** \| Klein's research shows pre-mortems increase accuracy of identifying reasons for outcomes by 30% \| · h2:Methodology Foundation=\| **Core Principle** \| "Prospective hindsight" - imagining an event has already occurred dramatically improves our ability to explain it. The future feels distant; the past feels real. \| · wh:Claude What You Decide=\| Claude Does \| You Decide \| · wh:Claude What You Decide=\|-------------\|------------\| · wh:Claude What You Decide=\| Structures production workflow \| Final creative direction \| · wh:Claude What You Decide=\| Suggests technical approaches \| Equipment and tool choices \| · wh:Claude What You Decide=\| Creates templates and checklists \| Quality standards \| · wh:Claude What You Decide=\| Identifies best practices \| Brand/voice decisions \| · wh:Claude What You Decide=\| Generates script outlines \| Final script approval \| · wh:This Skill Does=**Surfaces hidden risks** Finds dangers invisible forward-looking planning **Gives permission criticize** Team members voice concerns safely **Reduces overconfidence** Counters planning fallacy optimism bias **Improves plans before execution** Fix problems they're cheap fix **Creates psychological safety** "We're imagining failure" feels safer think fail" · h3:Run a Pre-Mortem=`Run a Pre-Mortem on this project: \· [describe the project, product, or decision] \·  \· It's one year from now and this has failed completely. What happened?` · h3:Stress-Test a Decision=`Pre-Mortem this decision: \· [describe the decision you're considering] \·  \· Assume we made this choice and it went badly. What went wrong?` · h3:Team Pre-Mortem Facilitation=`Help me facilitate a Pre-Mortem session for my team. \· Project: [description] \· Team size: [number] \· Time available: [duration] \· ` · in=facilitating Pre-Mortem, follow systematic process: · h3:Step Set Stage=`## Pre-Mortem Setup \·  \· **Project/Decision:** ________________________________ \·  \· **Timeline:** [Imagine we're looking back from X months/years]` · h3:Step Share Cluster=`## Round Robin Sharing \·  \· **Process:** \· 1. Each person shares ONE reason (no discussion yet) \· 2. Continue rounds until all reasons shared` · h3:Step Create Prevention/Mitigation Plans=`## Prevention Strategies \·  \· For each critical risk: \·  \· ### Risk: [Failure Reason 1]` · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=**Context:** SaaS company launching new enterprise product months. **Input:** "We're launching our enterprise product Q2. Everyone's excited. Run Pre-Mortem—what killed us?" **Output:** **The Scenario:** "It's September. Our enterprise launch failed. We've burned through our runway, product hasn't gained traction, we're considering pivot. What went wrong?" **Failure Reasons Generated:** **EXECUTION FAILURES:** underestimated enterprise sales cycle (6-12 months, Security review requirements didn't anticipate (SOC2, etc.) product wasn't actually enterprise-ready (missing audit logs, SSO) Support couldn't handle enterprise customer expectations **MARKET/TIMING:** Enterprise budgets frozen due economic conditions Two competitors launched similar products Target companies "wait see" mode **INTERNAL/TEAM:** Sales team enterprise experience Engineering bandwidth split between launch bug fixes 10. Marketing message didn't resonate enterprise buyers **RESOURCE:** 11. Ran out runway before enough deals closed 12. Couldn't hire enterprise sales rep fast enough **Risk Assessment:** · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=\| Failure Reason \| Likelihood \| Impact \| Priority \| · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=\|----------------\|------------\|--------\|----------\| · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=\| Enterprise sales cycle underestimated \| HIGH \| HIGH \| CRITICAL \| · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=\| Product not enterprise-ready \| HIGH \| HIGH \| CRITICAL \| · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=\| Budget freeze \| MEDIUM \| HIGH \| WATCH \| · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=\| Competitive launch \| MEDIUM \| MEDIUM \| MONITOR \| · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=\| Sales team inexperience \| HIGH \| HIGH \| CRITICAL \| · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=**Prevention Plan:** **Risk Sales Cycle Underestimated** · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=Prevention: Start enterprise conversations months early), Validation: LOIs before launch, "interested" calls, Tripwire: LOIs Week pause launch · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=**Risk Product Enterprise-Ready** · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=Prevention: Hire enterprise advisor audit requirements, Action: Prioritize SSO, audit logs, SLA before launch, Tripwire: security questionnaire failure, delay launch · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=**Risk Sales Team Inexperience** · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=Prevention: Hire one senior enterprise rep consultant, Alternative: Partner enterprise-focused reseller, Validation: Close one pilot before full launch · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=**Updated Plan:** · h3:Example Product Launch Pre-Mortem=Push launch (realistic timeline), Add SOC2 certification roadmap, Hire enterprise sales lead, Secure design partners before public launch · h3:Pre-Mortem Canvas=`┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ \· │                     PRE-MORTEM CANVAS                           │ \· ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ \· │                                                                 │ \· │  PROJECT: _________________________________________________    │` · h3:Pre-Mortem Question Bank=`## Pre-Mortem Prompts \·  \· Use these to stimulate thinking about different failure modes: \·  \· ### EXECUTION` · h2:Skill Metadata (Internal Use)=`name: pre-mortem \· category: strategy \· subcategory: risk-analysis \· version: 1.0 \· author: MKTG Skills`